Securing state file :
1. always use remote state for production
2. Enable encryption at rest
3. Implement access controls.
4. Enable state locking

Ephemeral values : Secrets that don't persist
Terraform 1.10+ require to use ephemeral = true

variable "exmaple" {
  description = "password of the database"
  type = string
  sensitive = true
  ephemeral = true
}

EPHEMERAL VALUES CAN BE USED :
Local values , provider blocks, ephemeral resources, ephemeral variables, 
ephemeral outputs, provisioner blocks, write-only arguments

USE CASE OF EPHEMERAL VALUES : 

variable "github token" {
  type = string
  description = ""
  sensitive = true
  ephemeral = true
}
provider "github" {
  owner = var.github_owner
  token = var.github_token
}

EPHEMERAL RESOURCES : New block type (not data or resource )
Fetches data at runtime and stored in memory
Never persisted in state and flushed when terraform operations are completed.
Opened and closed during execution
Use "ephemeral" keyword instead of "data"
Syntax is identical

When to use  :
- Fetching secrets from vault
- Reading temporary credentials
- Retrieving dynamic tokens

Write-Only Arguments : lets u securely pass temporary values to terraform's managed resources during an operation without persisting those values to state or plan files.
resource "" "" {
  instance_class = ""
  allocated_storage = ""
  engine = ""
  password_wo = "old pass"
  password_wo_version = 1
  
}









